The paper deals with probabilistic inference of UCQs (Unions of Conjunctive Queries) on tuple-independent databases. This topic falls under the domain of databases (cs.DB) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper proposes a new technique for constructing lineage representations as deterministic decomposable circuits, which involves computational complexity (cs.CC) and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the intensional approach for query evaluation, which involves probabilistic reasoning (cs.AI).
